Definition: a statutory offense that provides that it is a crime to knowingly cause another person to engage in an unwanted sexual act by force or threat
Example: most states have replaced the common law definition of rape with statutes defining sexual assault
Synonyms: sexual_abuse, sex_crime, sex_offense, statutory_offense, noun, group, law, c, a, statutory, offense, that, provides, it, is, crime, to, knowingly, cause, another, person, engage, in, an, unwanted, sexual, act, by, force, or, threat, most, states, have, replaced, the, common, definition, of, rape, with, statutes, defining, assault
Category: noun.act
